26
00:02:09,820 --> 00:02:15,360
So also, as we discussed, another important specification in a VAR

27
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:19,330
is deciding on the number of lags in the system.

28
00:02:19,330 --> 00:02:27,070
So opening up our VAR, let's note that EViews offers a number of useful tools

29
00:02:27,070 --> 00:02:30,650
to investigate the lag structure of the VAR.

30
00:02:30,650 --> 00:02:35,830
We can see that by going into "View, Lag Structure."

31
00:02:35,830 --> 00:02:39,590
We can do a lag exclusion test or a lag lengths criteria.

32
00:02:39,590 --> 00:02:45,220
Perhaps the most widely used is the lag lengths criteria.

33
00:02:45,220 --> 00:02:48,380
And the lag specification box opens up, which

34
00:02:48,380 --> 00:02:55,010
asks us what's the maximum number of lags for which we want to test.

35
00:02:55,010 --> 00:02:58,370
There are no hard rules here, but in general if you have monthly data

36
00:02:58,370 --> 00:03:03,010
you may want to set the number of lags to 12 or 24.

37
00:03:03,010 --> 00:03:06,040
If you have quarterly data, four or eight.

38
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:07,692
Let us select eight.

39
00:03:07,692 --> 00:03:13,610
And 1 or 2 for annual data, and then you'll click OK.

40
00:03:13,610 --> 00:03:16,690
The test results are shown here.

41
00:03:16,690 --> 00:03:20,700
So EViews denotes the appropriate lag lengths

42
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:24,680
for each criterion with an asterisk.

43
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:34,300
In this example, most tests seem to pick two as the appropriate lag length.

44
00:03:34,300 --> 00:03:40,230
Although the Schwarz criterion would choose one, and the likelihood ratio

45
00:03:40,230 --> 00:03:42,870
would choose five.

46
00:03:42,870 --> 00:03:46,890
Note that if there are no exogenous variables in the VAR,

47
00:03:46,890 --> 00:03:49,980
the count of the lag would start at one.

48
00:03:49,980 --> 00:03:55,590
Here since we selected the constant, the lag count starts at zero.

49
00:03:55,590 --> 00:03:59,060
Also note that you can replicate the results of these

50
00:03:59,060 --> 00:04:05,300
tests by typing in the command window this particular command.

51
